                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001/2–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-28">February 28,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received February 28—11:38 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>489. Acting President Li Tsung-jen requests following message be transmitted to
                    President: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Since assuming office as Acting President, I have had in mind a message
                            to you expressing the hope that the historic friendship between <pb
                                facs="0165" n="155" xml:id="pg_155"/> our countries may be
                            maintained, and assuring you of my appreciation for all that has been
                            done for China under your administration.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department 489, repeated AmEmbassy Canton 117.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
